headline: 3 Dividend Stocks On US Exchanges Yielding At Least 3%
summary: As the Federal Reserve's policy meeting on interest rates captures investor attention, stock futures indicate a cautious market with the Dow Jones poised for another potential decline. In this environment of fluctuating indices and economic uncertainty, dividend stocks yielding at least 3% can offer investors a measure of stability and income, making them an attractive option for those looking to balance risk with consistent returns.
